digraph kaya_bot_pipeline {
graph [
goal="Build AskKaya: full-stack client support platform with Go CLI (Bubble Tea TUI), Firebase backend (auth/billing/RAG), KB ingestion pipeline, Telegram escalation, Next.js admin dashboard, and Stripe billing",
retry_target="test_firebase",
default_max_retry=3,
rankdir=LR,
model_stylesheet="default=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929,fast=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001"
]

start [shape=Mdiamond, label="Start"]
done  [shape=Msquare, label="Done"]

// ── Setup ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

setup [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="setup", prompt="Set up the AskKaya monorepo in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate this directory structure:\n- cli/ — Go module (Cobra + Bubble Tea + Lipgloss)\n- firebase/functions/ — TypeScript Cloud Functions v2\n- firebase/firestore/ — Firestore rules + indexes\n- web/ — Next.js 14 app\n- config/.env.example — env var template\n- docs/ — documentation\n- package.json — monorepo root\n- pnpm-workspace.yaml — pnpm workspaces config\n- tsconfig.base.json — shared TS config\n\nSteps:\n1. Create root package.json with pnpm workspaces pointing to firebase/functions and web.\n2. Create pnpm-workspace.yaml listing firebase/functions and web.\n3. Create tsconfig.base.json with strict TS settings.\n4. Initialize Go module: cd cli && go mod init github.com/askkaya/cli\n5. Install Go deps: go get github.com/spf13/cobra@latest github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea@latest github.com/charmbracelet/lipgloss@latest github.com/charmbracelet/bubbles@latest github.com/zalando/go-keyring@latest\n6. Initialize firebase/functions: cd firebase/functions && pnpm init, then pnpm add firebase-admin firebase-functions openai @anthropic-ai/sdk stripe. Dev deps: pnpm add -D typescript jest ts-jest @types/jest @types/node.\n7. Create firebase/functions/tsconfig.json extending base config, target ES2021, module NodeNext.\n8. Create firebase/functions/src/index.ts as empty Cloud Functions entry point.\n9. Create config/.env.example with: OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID, STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, FIREBASE_API_KEY, GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET.\n10. Verify: cd cli && go build ./... (should succeed). cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit (should succeed).\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd cli && go vet ./...\n\nCommit: git add -A && git commit -m 'feat: initialize AskKaya monorepo with Go CLI, Firebase functions, and Next.js'"]

// ── Phase 1: Firebase Backend ─────────────────────────────────────────

test_firebase [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_firebase", prompt="Write ALL failing tests for the Firebase backend in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these test files under firebase/functions/__tests__/:\n\n1. unit/auth.test.ts — Auth middleware tests:\n   - Rejects requests with no Authorization header (401)\n   - Rejects requests with invalid Firebase ID token (401)\n   - Rejects requests with missing X-Client-ID header (400)\n   - Rejects requests where client document doesn't exist (404)\n   - Rejects requests where billing_status !== 'active' (403, message: 'Subscription inactive')\n   - Passes requests with valid token + active billing, attaches client to request context\n   - Records usage (increments query count for current month)\n   Import from: '../../src/middleware/auth'\n   Mock firebase-admin auth().verifyIdToken and firestore().collection\n\n2. unit/embeddings.test.ts — Embedding service tests:\n   - generateEmbedding(text) returns a number array\n   - generateEmbeddings(texts[]) returns array of vectors (batch)\n   - cosineSimilarity(a, b) returns correct similarity score\n   - Handles empty text input gracefully\n   - Handles API errors with retry (1 retry, then throw)\n   Import from: '../../src/services/embeddings'\n\n3. unit/rag.test.ts — RAG service tests:\n   - retrieveContext(clientId, queryEmbedding, setupContext) searches both global and per-client KB\n   - Per-client articles get 30% score boost over global\n   - Articles matching client setup_context tags get additional weight\n   - Returns top-K results (K=5) sorted by relevance\n   - Returns empty array when no articles above threshold (0.3)\n   - Handles missing client KB gracefully\n   Types: RetrievalResult { articleId, title, summary, content, score, source: 'global' | 'client' }\n   Import from: '../../src/services/rag'\n\n4. unit/generation.test.ts — Generation service tests:\n   - generateResponse(query, context[], clientName) returns { text, confidence, sources, shouldEscalate }\n   - Confidence > 0.7: normal response\n   - Confidence 0.4-0.7: response with low confidence flag\n   - Confidence < 0.4: triggers escalation\n   - Uses Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929 for generation)\n   - Sources array contains article IDs\n   Import from: '../../src/services/generation'\n\n5. unit/tickets.test.ts — Ticket service tests:\n   - createTicket(clientId, clientName, query, context) creates escalation with status 'pending'\n   - getTicket(ticketId) returns ticket or null\n   - answerTicket(ticketId, response) updates to 'answered'\n   - listPendingTickets() returns pending ordered by created_at DESC\n   - closeTicket(ticketId) sets status 'closed'\n   Import from: '../../src/services/tickets'\n\n6. integration/query-pipeline.test.ts — Integration test:\n   - Seed Firestore with client (active billing) and KB articles\n   - POST /api/query with valid auth returns { text, confidence, sources }\n   - Low confidence query creates escalation ticket\n   - Suspended billing returns 403\n\nShared types used across tests:\n  Client { id, name, email, api_key, billing_status: 'active'|'suspended'|'cancelled', setup_context: string[], monthly_query_limit, stripe_customer_id? }\n  KnowledgeArticle { id, title, summary, content, client_context: string[], source_refs: string[], embedding: number[], auto_generated }\n  Escalation { id, client_id, client_name, query, context, status: 'pending'|'answered'|'closed', kaya_response?, notification_channel? }\n  QueryResponse { text, confidence, sources: string[], escalated }\n\nEvery test MUST fail initially (modules not yet implemented).\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose (expect all FAIL)\n\nCommit: git add firebase/functions/__tests__/ && git commit -m 'test: add failing tests for Firebase backend Phase 1'"]

impl_firebase [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_firebase", prompt="Implement the Firebase backend to make all Phase 1 tests pass. Work in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these files under firebase/functions/src/:\n\n1. middleware/auth.ts — Auth middleware:\n   - Extract Bearer token from Authorization header\n   - Verify token with admin.auth().verifyIdToken(token)\n   - Extract client ID from X-Client-ID header\n   - Fetch client document from Firestore clients/{clientId}\n   - Check billing_status === 'active' — if not, return 403 'Subscription inactive' (hard cutoff, no grace)\n   - Attach client data to req.client\n   - Increment usage counter for current month (fire-and-forget)\n   - Call next()\n\n2. services/embeddings.ts — OpenAI embedding service:\n   - generateEmbedding(text: string): Promise<number[]> — uses text-embedding-3-small\n   - generateEmbeddings(texts: string[]): Promise<number[][]> — batch\n   - cosineSimilarity(a: number[], b: number[]): number\n   - Uses openai npm package, API key from process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY\n\n3. services/rag.ts — RAG retrieval:\n   - retrieveContext(clientId, queryEmbedding, setupContext): Promise<RetrievalResult[]>\n   - Search global KB: knowledge_base/global/articles\n   - Search client KB: knowledge_base/clients/{clientId}/articles\n   - Per-client articles get 30% score boost\n   - setup_context tag matches get additional weight\n   - Return top-5 results above 0.3 threshold\n\n4. services/generation.ts — Claude API generation:\n   - generateResponse(query, context[], clientName): Promise<{ text, confidence, sources, shouldEscalate }>\n   - Uses claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929 via @anthropic-ai/sdk\n   - System prompt: 'You are AskKaya, a support assistant for {clientName}. Answer using ONLY the provided context.'\n   - Confidence < 0.4 triggers escalation\n\n5. services/tickets.ts — Escalation CRUD:\n   - createTicket, getTicket, answerTicket, listPendingTickets, closeTicket\n   - Firestore collection: escalations/{ticketId}\n\n6. api/query.ts — Query endpoint (Cloud Function v2 onRequest):\n   - Wire: auth middleware -> embed query -> RAG retrieve -> generate -> optional escalation -> return response\n   - POST only, 400 if no query\n\n7. api/health.ts — Health endpoint:\n   - Returns { status: 'ok', timestamp: ISO string }\n\n8. index.ts — Export query and health functions\n\nCommit after each major service. Use conventional commits:\n- 'feat: add auth middleware with billing gate hard cutoff'\n- 'feat: add OpenAI embedding service with batch support'\n- 'feat: add RAG retrieval with client context boosting'\n- 'feat: add Claude-powered response generation'\n- 'feat: add escalation ticket service'\n- 'feat: add query endpoint wiring full pipeline'\n\nQuality checks after each commit:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose"]

verify_firebase [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_firebase", prompt="Verify all Phase 1 Firebase backend tests pass in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nRun these commands:\n1. cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit (TypeScript compilation must succeed with zero errors)\n2. cd firebase/functions && npx jest __tests__/unit/ --verbose (all unit tests must pass)\n3. cd firebase/functions && firebase emulators:exec 'npx jest __tests__/integration/query-pipeline.test.ts --verbose' --only firestore,auth (integration tests against emulator)\n\nAll tests must pass. Report outcome=SUCCESS if every test passes, outcome=FAIL if any test fails.\n\nIf tests fail, report which tests failed and why."]

verify_firebase_ok [shape=diamond, label="Firebase tests pass?"]

// ── Phase 2: Go CLI ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

test_cli [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_cli", prompt="Write ALL failing tests for the Go CLI in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these test files under cli/:\n\n1. internal/auth/client_test.go — Firebase Auth REST client tests:\n   - SignIn(email, password) calls Firebase Identity Toolkit REST API, returns AuthTokens{IDToken, RefreshToken, ExpiresIn, ExpiresAt}\n   - POST https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com/v1/accounts:signInWithPassword?key={API_KEY}\n   - RefreshToken(refreshToken) exchanges refresh token for new ID token\n   - POST https://securetoken.googleapis.com/v1/token?key={API_KEY}\n   - GetCurrentToken() returns valid token or refreshes if expired\n   - Handles invalid credentials with descriptive error\n   - Handles network errors\n   Use httptest.NewServer for mocking HTTP calls.\n\n2. internal/auth/keychain_test.go — Keychain storage tests:\n   - StoreTokens(tokens) saves to OS keychain under service 'askkaya'\n   - LoadTokens() retrieves from keychain, returns error if not found\n   - ClearTokens() removes from keychain\n   Use github.com/zalando/go-keyring\n\n3. internal/api/client_test.go — Firebase Functions API client tests:\n   - Query(question) sends POST to /api/query with Authorization and X-Client-ID headers\n   - Returns QueryResponse{Text, Confidence, Sources, Escalated}\n   - HealthCheck() sends GET to /api/health\n   - Auto-refreshes token on 401 (one retry)\n   - Returns structured error on 403 (billing suspended)\n   - Handles network timeouts (10s default)\n   Use httptest.NewServer for mocking.\n\n4. internal/tui/app_test.go — Bubble Tea TUI tests using teatest:\n   - App starts on login screen if no stored token\n   - App starts on query screen if authenticated\n   - Login screen accepts email/password input\n   - Query screen accepts text input, sends query, displays response\n   - Response shows text, confidence indicator, sources\n   - Error states render correctly\n   Use github.com/charmbracelet/x/exp/teatest\n\n5. internal/heartbeat/daemon_test.go — Heartbeat tests:\n   - Daemon.Start() begins periodic health checks\n   - Daemon.Stop() stops the loop\n   - Detects expired auth token, logs warning\n   - Detects suspended billing, logs warning\n\nAll tests MUST fail initially.\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd cli && go vet ./...\n- Run: cd cli && go test ./... -v (expect all FAIL)\n\nCommit: git add cli/ && git commit -m 'test: add failing tests for Go CLI Phase 2'"]

impl_cli [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_cli", prompt="Implement the Go CLI to make all Phase 2 tests pass. Work in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these files under cli/:\n\n1. cmd/root.go — Cobra root command with version flag, config path ~/.config/askkaya/\n2. main.go — calls cmd.Execute()\n\n3. internal/auth/client.go — Firebase Auth REST client:\n   - AuthClient struct with APIKey, HTTPClient\n   - SignIn(email, password) -> (*AuthTokens, error)\n   - RefreshToken(refreshToken) -> (*AuthTokens, error)\n   - AuthTokens struct: IDToken, RefreshToken, ExpiresIn, ExpiresAt\n\n4. internal/auth/keychain.go — OS keychain token storage:\n   - StoreTokens, LoadTokens, ClearTokens using github.com/zalando/go-keyring\n   - Service name: 'askkaya'\n\n5. internal/api/client.go — Firebase Functions HTTP client:\n   - APIClient struct with BaseURL, ClientID, Auth, HTTPClient\n   - Query(question) -> (*QueryResponse, error) — POST /api/query with Bearer token + X-Client-ID\n   - HealthCheck() -> error — GET /api/health\n   - Auto-refresh on 401, structured error on 403\n\n6. cmd/auth.go — auth login (prompts email/password or takes flags), auth logout (clears keychain)\n7. cmd/query.go — query 'question' sends query, prints formatted response\n8. cmd/status.go — shows auth status, billing, connectivity\n\n9. internal/tui/app.go — Root Bubble Tea model with state machine: LoginScreen -> QueryScreen -> LoadingScreen -> ResponseScreen\n10. internal/tui/login.go — Auth TUI\n11. internal/tui/query.go — Query input + response display\n12. internal/tui/status.go — Status display\n13. internal/tui/styles.go — Lipgloss styles: response box (bordered), confidence indicator (green>0.7, yellow 0.4-0.7, red<0.4), sources (dimmed), error (red bordered)\n\n14. internal/heartbeat/daemon.go — Background health check (configurable interval, default 5 min)\n15. internal/heartbeat/launchd.go — macOS launchd plist management for ~/Library/LaunchAgents/\n16. cmd/heartbeat.go — heartbeat start/stop/install/uninstall commands\n\n17. cmd/skill.go — OpenClaw skill registration:\n    - 'askkaya skill register' outputs skill definition JSON\n    - 'askkaya skill query question' accepts piped input, returns JSON response\n\nCommit after each major component with conventional commits.\n\nQuality checks after each commit:\n- Run: cd cli && go vet ./...\n- Run: cd cli && go test ./... -v"]

verify_cli [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_cli", prompt="Verify all Phase 2 Go CLI tests pass in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nRun these commands:\n1. cd cli && go vet ./... (must pass with zero warnings)\n2. cd cli && go build -o askkaya . (must compile successfully)\n3. cd cli && go test ./... -v (all unit tests must pass)\n4. cd cli && ./askkaya --help (smoke test: must print help text)\n\nAll tests must pass. Report outcome=SUCCESS if every test passes, outcome=FAIL if any test fails.\n\nIf tests fail, report which tests failed and why."]

verify_cli_ok [shape=diamond, label="CLI tests pass?"]

// ── Phase 3: Knowledge Base Pipeline ──────────────────────────────────

test_kb [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_kb", prompt="Write ALL failing tests for the KB ingestion pipeline in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these test files under firebase/functions/__tests__/:\n\n1. unit/webhook.test.ts — GitHub webhook receiver:\n   - Verifies GitHub webhook signature (X-Hub-Signature-256) using HMAC-SHA256\n   - Rejects invalid signature (401)\n   - Parses push event, extracts added/modified .md files only\n   - Ignores non-.md and deleted files\n   - Maps paths: global/ -> global KB, clients/{name}/ -> per-client KB\n   Types: FileToProcess { path, content, target: 'global' | { clientId: string } }\n   Import from: '../../src/processing/webhook'\n\n2. unit/parser.test.ts — Markdown parser:\n   - Extracts YAML frontmatter if present\n   - Extracts heading hierarchy\n   - Identifies document types: transcript, setup_notes, documentation, general\n   - Returns ParsedDocument { title, frontmatter, sections: Section[], documentType }\n   - Section { heading, level, content }\n   Import from: '../../src/processing/parser'\n\n3. unit/chunker.test.ts — Semantic chunker:\n   - Splits ParsedDocument into ~500 token chunks (word count / 0.75)\n   - Preserves section boundaries\n   - Each chunk includes heading context breadcrumb ('Setup > VAPI > Webhooks')\n   - 50 token overlap between chunks\n   - Handles very short docs (single chunk)\n   - Handles very long sections (splits at paragraph boundaries)\n   Types: Chunk { text, headingContext, index, totalChunks, sourceRef }\n   Import from: '../../src/processing/chunker'\n\n4. unit/embedder.test.ts — Batch embedder:\n   - embedChunks(chunks[]) generates embeddings for all chunks\n   - Batches API calls (max 20 per batch)\n   - Returns EmbeddedChunk (Chunk + embedding: number[])\n   - Handles partial failures with retry (2 attempts)\n   Import from: '../../src/processing/embedder'\n\n5. unit/articulator.test.ts — Article articulator:\n   - articulateArticle(chunks[], sourceRef) generates structured KB article via Claude Haiku\n   - Returns { title, summary, content, client_context: string[], source_refs, embedding, auto_generated: true }\n   - Groups related chunks before articulation\n   Import from: '../../src/processing/articulator'\n\n6. unit/indexer.test.ts — Firestore indexer:\n   - indexArticle(article, 'global') stores in knowledge_base/global/articles/{id}\n   - indexArticle(article, { clientId }) stores in knowledge_base/clients/{clientId}/articles/{id}\n   - Generates unique ID from title slug + timestamp\n   - Upserts if source_ref matches\n   Import from: '../../src/processing/indexer'\n\n7. integration/kb-ingest.test.ts — Full pipeline integration:\n   - Simulate GitHub webhook push with .md file\n   - Verify article appears in Firestore with embedding, title, summary\n   - Verify RAG retrieval finds the new article\n\nAll tests MUST fail initially.\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose (expect FAIL for new tests)\n\nCommit: git add firebase/functions/__tests__/ && git commit -m 'test: add failing tests for KB ingestion pipeline Phase 3'"]

impl_kb [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_kb", prompt="Implement the KB ingestion pipeline to make all Phase 3 tests pass. Work in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these files under firebase/functions/src/processing/:\n\n1. webhook.ts — GitHub webhook receiver (Cloud Function v2 onRequest):\n   - Verify signature using HMAC-SHA256 with process.env.GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET\n   - Parse push event payload, filter for added/modified .md files\n   - Fetch file content from GitHub API\n   - Map directory structure to target: global/ -> 'global', clients/{name}/ -> { clientId }\n   - Export: handleGitHubWebhook(req) -> { files: FileToProcess[], skipped: number }\n\n2. parser.ts — Markdown structure extraction:\n   - Extract YAML frontmatter (between --- markers)\n   - Parse heading hierarchy (# through ####)\n   - Detect document type by content patterns\n   - Export: parseMarkdown(content, filename) -> ParsedDocument\n\n3. chunker.ts — Semantic text chunking:\n   - Target ~500 tokens per chunk (rough: word count / 0.75)\n   - Respect section boundaries, split long sections at paragraph breaks\n   - Include heading breadcrumb context in each chunk\n   - 50 token overlap for continuity\n   - Export: chunkDocument(doc: ParsedDocument, sourceRef: string) -> Chunk[]\n\n4. embedder.ts — Batch embedding generation:\n   - Batch chunks into groups of 20 max\n   - Use embeddings service (generateEmbeddings) from services/embeddings.ts\n   - Retry failed batches once\n   - Export: embedChunks(chunks: Chunk[]) -> EmbeddedChunk[]\n\n5. articulator.ts — LLM article generation:\n   - Use Claude Haiku (claude-haiku-4-5-20251001) for speed/cost\n   - System prompt: 'You are a technical writer creating a KB article from raw notes. Create: title, 1-2 sentence summary, well-organized content with headers, client_context tags.'\n   - Export: articulateArticle(chunks: EmbeddedChunk[], sourceRef: string) -> KnowledgeArticle (without id/timestamps)\n\n6. indexer.ts — Firestore storage:\n   - Store in correct collection based on target\n   - Generate ID from title slug + timestamp\n   - Upsert: if existing article has same source_ref, update it\n   - Store raw dump in raw_dumps/ subcollection\n   - Export: indexArticle(article, target) -> string (article ID)\n\nModify firebase/functions/src/index.ts to export the GitHub webhook function.\n\nCommit after each component with conventional commits.\n\nQuality checks after each commit:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose"]

verify_kb [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_kb", prompt="Verify all Phase 3 KB pipeline tests pass in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nRun these commands:\n1. cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit (zero errors)\n2. cd firebase/functions && npx jest __tests__/unit/webhook.test.ts __tests__/unit/parser.test.ts __tests__/unit/chunker.test.ts __tests__/unit/embedder.test.ts __tests__/unit/articulator.test.ts __tests__/unit/indexer.test.ts --verbose\n3. cd firebase/functions && firebase emulators:exec 'npx jest __tests__/integration/kb-ingest.test.ts --verbose' --only firestore,auth\n\nAll tests must pass. Report outcome=SUCCESS if every test passes, outcome=FAIL if any test fails."]

verify_kb_ok [shape=diamond, label="KB pipeline tests pass?"]

// ── Phase 4: Notifications ───────────────────────────────────────────

test_notify [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_notify", prompt="Write ALL failing tests for the notification system in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these test files under firebase/functions/__tests__/:\n\n1. unit/telegram.test.ts — Telegram bot:\n   - formatEscalationAlert(escalation) returns formatted message with client name, query, context tags\n   - sendMessage(chatId, text) calls Telegram Bot API POST https://api.telegram.org/bot{TOKEN}/sendMessage\n   - handleTelegramUpdate(update) processes reply messages: extracts answer, calls answerTicket, triggers auto-learn, sends confirmation\n   - Handles Telegram API errors with 1 retry\n   Env vars: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID\n   Import from: '../../src/notify/telegram'\n\n2. unit/router.test.ts — Notification router:\n   - sendNotification(escalation) tries channels in order: telegram -> imessage -> email\n   - If primary succeeds, skips fallbacks\n   - If primary fails, tries next channel\n   - Records which channel was used on escalation document\n   - Returns { sent: boolean, channel: string }\n   Import from: '../../src/notify/router'\n\n3. integration/escalation.test.ts — Full escalation flow:\n   - Create escalation ticket in Firestore\n   - Verify notification trigger fires\n   - Simulate Telegram reply (call webhook handler)\n   - Verify ticket status updated to 'answered'\n   - Verify new KB article created from the answer (auto-learn)\n   - Verify answer retrievable via RAG\n\nAll tests MUST fail initially.\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose (expect FAIL for new tests)\n\nCommit: git add firebase/functions/__tests__/ && git commit -m 'test: add failing tests for notification system Phase 4'"]

impl_notify [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_notify", prompt="Implement the notification system to make all Phase 4 tests pass. Work in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these files under firebase/functions/src/notify/:\n\n1. telegram.ts — Telegram Bot API integration:\n   - formatEscalationAlert(escalation: Escalation) -> string (formatted message with client name, query, context)\n   - sendMessage(chatId: string, text: string) -> Promise<void> (POST to https://api.telegram.org/bot{TOKEN}/sendMessage)\n   - handleTelegramUpdate(update) — process reply: extract answer, call answerTicket(), trigger auto-learn (create KB article from answer, generate embedding, index in client KB), send confirmation\n   - Env vars: process.env.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, process.env.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID\n\n2. imessage.ts — iMessage bridge (fallback):\n   - sendIMMessage(phoneNumber, message) -> Promise<boolean>\n   - HTTP call to configurable webhook URL for local bridge\n\n3. router.ts — Channel priority routing:\n   - sendNotification(escalation: Escalation) -> Promise<{ sent: boolean, channel: string }>\n   - Try telegram first, then imessage, then email\n   - Record channel on escalation Firestore document\n\nModify firebase/functions/src/index.ts:\n- Add Firestore onCreate trigger for escalations/{ticketId}:\n  import { onDocumentCreated } from 'firebase-functions/v2/firestore'\n  On new escalation, call sendNotification(escalation)\n- Add Telegram webhook endpoint (onRequest)\n\nAuto-learn pipeline (triggered when answerTicket is called):\n1. Take answer text + original query\n2. Create KB article: title from query, content from answer\n3. Generate embedding via embeddings service\n4. Index in client KB collection via indexer\n\nCommit after each component with conventional commits.\n\nQuality checks after each commit:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose"]

verify_notify [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_notify", prompt="Verify all Phase 4 notification tests pass in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nRun these commands:\n1. cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit (zero errors)\n2. cd firebase/functions && npx jest __tests__/unit/telegram.test.ts __tests__/unit/router.test.ts --verbose\n3. cd firebase/functions && firebase emulators:exec 'npx jest __tests__/integration/escalation.test.ts --verbose' --only firestore,auth\n\nAll tests must pass. Report outcome=SUCCESS if every test passes, outcome=FAIL if any test fails."]

verify_notify_ok [shape=diamond, label="Notification tests pass?"]

// ── Phase 5: Web Dashboard ───────────────────────────────────────────

test_web [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_web", prompt="Write ALL failing tests for the Next.js admin dashboard in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these test files under web/__tests__/:\n\n1. login.test.tsx — Auth + login:\n   - Login page renders email/password form\n   - Firebase Auth signInWithEmailAndPassword called on submit\n   - Redirects to /dashboard on success\n   - Shows error on invalid credentials\n   - Protected routes redirect to /login if unauthenticated\n   - Rejects non-admin users (missing admin:true custom claim)\n\n2. dashboard.test.tsx — Dashboard page:\n   - Renders recent query count (last 24h)\n   - Renders active escalation count\n   - Renders client count\n   - Renders billing summary (active vs suspended)\n   Uses Server Components fetching from Firestore\n\n3. clients.test.tsx — Client management:\n   - Client list shows all clients with name, status, setup_context tags\n   - Client detail shows full info + per-client KB article count + recent queries\n   - Create form with name, email, setup_context tags\n   - Edit updates Firestore document\n\n4. kb.test.tsx — KB browser:\n   - Lists all articles (global + per-client) with title, summary, source\n   - Search filters by title/content text match\n   - Filter by client or global\n   - Article viewer shows full content with metadata\n   - Re-process button triggers re-indexing\n\n5. escalations.test.tsx — Escalation queue:\n   - Lists tickets filtered by status (pending/answered/closed)\n   - Ticket detail shows client name, query, context, timestamps\n   - Reply form submits answer, updates status, triggers auto-learn\n   - Close button marks ticket as closed\n\n6. analytics.test.tsx — Analytics page:\n   - Renders query volume chart (per day, last 30 days)\n   - Renders confidence distribution histogram\n   - Renders escalation rate percentage\n   - Renders top queried topics\n\nTech: Next.js 14 App Router, React Testing Library, jest, Firebase client + admin SDK.\n\nAll tests MUST fail initially.\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd web && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd web && npx jest --verbose (expect FAIL)\n\nCommit: git add web/__tests__/ && git commit -m 'test: add failing tests for Next.js admin dashboard Phase 5'"]

impl_web [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_web", prompt="Implement the Next.js admin dashboard to make all Phase 5 tests pass. Work in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nFirst, initialize Next.js if not already done:\n  cd web && npx create-next-app@latest . --typescript --tailwind --app --src-dir=false --import-alias='@/*'\n  pnpm add firebase firebase-admin recharts\n  pnpm add -D @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom jest @types/jest\n\nCreate these files:\n\n1. lib/firebase.ts — Client-side Firebase init (for auth in browser)\n2. lib/firebase-admin.ts — Server-side admin SDK (for Firestore in Server Components)\n3. lib/types.ts — Shared TypeScript types (Client, KnowledgeArticle, Escalation, UsageRecord, QueryResponse)\n\n4. app/layout.tsx — Root layout with sidebar navigation: Dashboard, Clients, Knowledge Base, Escalations, Analytics\n5. app/page.tsx — Redirect to /dashboard\n6. middleware.ts — Route protection: redirect to /login if unauthenticated, check admin:true custom claim\n\n7. app/login/page.tsx — Email/password login form using Firebase Auth\n8. app/dashboard/page.tsx — Server Component: fetch stats from Firestore (query count 24h, escalation count, client count, billing summary)\n\n9. app/clients/page.tsx + [clientId]/page.tsx — Client list and detail pages\n10. components/clients/client-list.tsx, client-form.tsx, client-card.tsx\n\n11. app/knowledge-base/page.tsx — KB browser with search\n12. components/kb/article-list.tsx, article-viewer.tsx, search-bar.tsx\n\n13. app/escalations/page.tsx — Escalation queue with status filter\n14. components/escalations/ticket-list.tsx, ticket-detail.tsx, reply-form.tsx\n    Reply form: submit answer -> update ticket status -> trigger auto-learn\n\n15. app/analytics/page.tsx — Analytics with recharts\n16. components/analytics/query-chart.tsx, confidence-chart.tsx\n\nCommit after each major page with conventional commits.\n\nQuality checks after each commit:\n- Run: cd web && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd web && npx jest --verbose\n- Run: cd web && npx next build (must succeed)"]

verify_web [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_web", prompt="Verify all Phase 5 web dashboard tests pass in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nRun these commands:\n1. cd web && npx tsc --noEmit (zero errors)\n2. cd web && npx jest --verbose (all component and route tests must pass)\n3. cd web && npx next build (build must succeed without errors)\n\nAll tests must pass and build must succeed. Report outcome=SUCCESS if everything passes, outcome=FAIL if anything fails."]

verify_web_ok [shape=diamond, label="Web dashboard tests pass?"]

// ── Phase 6: Billing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

test_billing [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_billing", prompt="Write ALL failing tests for Stripe billing integration in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these test files under firebase/functions/__tests__/:\n\n1. unit/stripe.test.ts — Stripe webhook handlers:\n   - Verifies Stripe signature using stripe.webhooks.constructEvent()\n   - invoice.paid -> sets client billing_status = 'active'\n   - invoice.payment_failed -> sets billing_status = 'suspended' immediately (NO grace period)\n   - customer.subscription.deleted -> sets billing_status = 'cancelled'\n   - Maps Stripe customer ID to client ID via stripe_customer_id field\n   - Ignores unknown event types (returns 200)\n   - Rejects invalid signatures (400)\n   Import from: '../../src/billing/stripe'\n\n2. unit/gate.test.ts — Billing gate:\n   - checkBilling(clientId) returns { allowed: boolean, reason?: string }\n   - active -> { allowed: true }\n   - suspended -> { allowed: false, reason: 'Subscription inactive' }\n   - Quota exceeded -> { allowed: false, reason: 'Monthly query limit reached' }\n   Import from: '../../src/billing/gate'\n\n3. unit/usage.test.ts — Usage tracking:\n   - recordUsage(clientId) increments query count for current month\n   - getUsage(clientId) returns current month usage\n   - Usage key format: months.{YYYY-MM}.count\n   Import from: '../../src/billing/usage'\n\n4. integration/billing.test.ts — Full billing integration:\n   - Create client with billing_status 'active', monthly_query_limit 10\n   - Send query -> succeeds\n   - Simulate invoice.payment_failed webhook -> billing_status = 'suspended'\n   - Send query -> 403 'Subscription inactive'\n   - Simulate invoice.paid webhook -> billing_status = 'active'\n   - Send query -> succeeds\n   - Send 10 queries to exhaust quota\n   - Send 11th -> rejected 'Monthly query limit reached'\n\nAll tests MUST fail initially.\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose (expect FAIL for new tests)\n\nCommit: git add firebase/functions/__tests__/ && git commit -m 'test: add failing tests for Stripe billing Phase 6'"]

impl_billing [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_billing", prompt="Implement Stripe billing to make all Phase 6 tests pass. Work in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate these files under firebase/functions/src/billing/:\n\n1. stripe.ts — Stripe webhook handlers:\n   - handleStripeWebhook(req) -> { received: boolean }\n   - Verify signature: stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(body, sig, process.env.STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET)\n   - invoice.paid -> update clients/{clientId} billing_status = 'active' (lookup by stripe_customer_id)\n   - invoice.payment_failed -> billing_status = 'suspended' immediately, no grace period\n   - customer.subscription.deleted -> billing_status = 'cancelled'\n   - Unknown events -> return 200, ignore\n   - Use stripe npm package\n\n2. gate.ts — Billing gate module:\n   - checkBilling(clientId) -> { allowed: boolean, reason?: string }\n   - Fetch client from Firestore\n   - Check billing_status === 'active'\n   - Check monthly usage < monthly_query_limit\n   - Refactor auth middleware to use this module\n\n3. usage.ts — Usage tracking:\n   - recordUsage(clientId) -> increments usage/{clientId}.months.{YYYY-MM}.count using FieldValue.increment(1)\n   - getUsage(clientId) -> returns current month count\n   - resetMonthlyQuotas() — scheduled function (0 0 1 * *) for monthly reset (or let month key roll over)\n\nModify firebase/functions/src/index.ts:\n- Export Stripe webhook endpoint\n- Export scheduled quota reset function (onSchedule from firebase-functions/v2/scheduler)\n\nCommit after each component with conventional commits.\n\nQuality checks after each commit:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose"]

verify_billing [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_billing", prompt="Verify all Phase 6 billing tests pass in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nRun these commands:\n1. cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit (zero errors)\n2. cd firebase/functions && npx jest __tests__/unit/stripe.test.ts __tests__/unit/gate.test.ts __tests__/unit/usage.test.ts --verbose\n3. cd firebase/functions && firebase emulators:exec 'npx jest __tests__/integration/billing.test.ts --verbose' --only firestore,auth\n\nAll tests must pass. Report outcome=SUCCESS if every test passes, outcome=FAIL if any test fails."]

verify_billing_ok [shape=diamond, label="Billing tests pass?"]

// ── Integration & Release ────────────────────────────────────────────

integration_test [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="test_firebase", prompt="Run full E2E integration test across all components in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\nCreate tests/e2e/full-pipeline.test.ts (or shell script) that tests against Firebase emulator:\n\n1. Setup: Seed Firestore with client (active billing, setup_context: ['vapi']) and global KB articles\n2. CLI Auth: Verify askkaya auth login works with test credentials against emulator\n3. Query (high confidence): POST /api/query with VAPI question -> response with sources\n4. Query (low confidence): POST /api/query with off-topic question -> 'Let me check with Kaya' + escalation\n5. Escalation: Verify ticket exists in Firestore with status 'pending'\n6. Notification: Verify Telegram notification triggered (check logs)\n7. Auto-learn: Simulate Telegram reply -> ticket updated, new KB article created\n8. KB ingestion: POST GitHub webhook with .md file -> article appears in Firestore\n9. Web dashboard: cd web && npx next build (verify build succeeds)\n10. Billing cutoff: Suspend client in Firestore -> query returns 403\n\nRun with: firebase emulators:exec 'npx jest tests/e2e/ --verbose' --only firestore,auth\n\nReport outcome=SUCCESS if all pass, outcome=FAIL if any fail."]

integration_ok [shape=diamond, label="Integration tests pass?"]

polish [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="polish", prompt="Polish and harden the AskKaya codebase in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\n1. Tighten Firestore rules to least-privilege (review firebase/firestore/firestore.rules)\n2. Tune RAG parameters in firebase/functions/src/services/rag.ts: similarity threshold (0.3), top-K (5), client boost (30%)\n3. Tune confidence thresholds in firebase/functions/src/services/generation.ts: escalation (0.65), critical (0.4)\n4. Add rate limiting to query endpoint (100 req/min per client)\n5. Verify PII redaction in responses (no email/phone in generated text)\n6. Add structured logging (JSON format for Cloud Logging) across all Cloud Functions\n7. Clean up TODO comments\n\nQuality checks:\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx tsc --noEmit\n- Run: cd firebase/functions && npx jest --verbose\n- Run: cd cli && go vet ./... && go test ./... -v\n- Run: cd web && npx tsc --noEmit && npx next build\n\nCommit: git commit -m 'chore: polish and harden for production'"]

release [shape=box, goal_gate=true, retry_target="release", prompt="Prepare AskKaya for release in the run working directory (context key run.working_dir).\n\n1. Firebase deployment config: verify firebase.json has functions, firestore rules, hosting config for web/\n2. Go CLI cross-compilation:\n   - GOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o dist/askkaya-darwin-arm64 ./cli\n   - GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o dist/askkaya-darwin-amd64 ./cli\n   - GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o dist/askkaya-linux-amd64 ./cli\n3. Homebrew formula: verify cli/Formula/askkaya.rb is correct\n4. Environment variable checklist: verify config/.env.example has all required secrets\n5. Create docs/ARCHITECTURE.md with system overview\n6. Create operator runbook covering: client onboarding, billing lifecycle, escalation workflow, KB management\n\nQuality checks:\n- All binaries build without errors\n- firebase deploy --only firestore:rules --dry-run succeeds\n- All tests still pass\n\nCommit: git commit -m 'chore: prepare release artifacts and documentation'"]

